            207 =>
            array (
                'id' => 235,
                'name' => 'Affenpinscher',
                'slug' => 'affenpinscher',
                'description' => NULL,
                'min_life' => 14,
                'max_life' => 16,
                'male_weight_max' => 5,
                'male_weight_min' => 3,
                'female_weight_max' => 5,
                'female_weight_min' => 3,
                'content' => NULL,
                'history_description' => '<p>The Affenpinscher is a toy breed that originated in Germany, with a history dating back to the 1600s. The name "Affenpinscher" means "Monkey Terrier" in German, reflecting their distinctive appearance and playful personality. They were initially bred to control pests in homes and stables, serving as effective ratters. Over time, they gained popularity as companion animals, particularly among nobles and the bourgeoisie.</p>',
                'size_description' => '<p>Affenpinschers are small dogs, typically standing between 9 to 11.5 inches tall at the shoulder. Their weight usually ranges from 6 to 13 pounds, making them a suitable breed for apartment living and small households.</p>',
                'coat_description' => '<p>The Affenpinscher has a wiry, dense, and harsh coat that gives them a distinctive look. Their fur is usually black, but they can also come in gray, silver, black-and-tan, or even red. Regular grooming is necessary to maintain the health and appearance of their coat, including brushing to prevent matting.</p>',
                'temperament_description' => '<p>Affenpinschers are known for their spirited and confident nature. They are outgoing, curious, and often exhibit a sense of humor. These dogs can be stubborn at times, but they are also loyal and affectionate toward their families. They are generally good with children and can get along well with other pets if properly socialized.</p>',
                'lifestyle_description' => '<p>Affenpinschers adapt well to various living situations, including apartments and smaller homes, provided they receive adequate exercise and mental stimulation. They thrive on interaction with their owners and enjoy being involved in family activities.</p>',
                'activities_description' => '<p>Fun activities for Affenpinschers include short walks, playtime in the yard, and interactive games such as fetch or tug-of-war. They also enjoy participation in dog shows and activities like obedience training or agility courses that challenge their intelligence and energy. Socialization with other dogs and exposure to different environments are essential to help them develop into well-rounded pets.</p>',
                'hypoallergenic' => true,
                'created_at' => '2024-11-14 22:09:53',
                'updated_at' => '2024-11-14 22:13:17',
            ),
            208 =>
            array (
                'id' => 236,
                'name' => 'Skye Terrier',
                'slug' => 'skye-terrier',
                'description' => NULL,
                'min_life' => 12,
                'max_life' => 15,
                'male_weight_max' => 8,
                'male_weight_min' => 7,
                'female_weight_max' => 8,
                'female_weight_min' => 7,
                'content' => NULL,
                'history_description' => '<p>The Skye Terrier is a Scottish breed that originated on the Isle of Skye. They were primarily used as working dogs to hunt vermin and small game, particularly otters and foxes. The breed dates back to the 16th century and has connections to nobility, with some historical figures, like Queen Victoria, owning them, which helped raise their profile in society.</p>',
                'size_description' => '<p>Skye Terriers are small to medium-sized dogs, typically weighing between 25-40 pounds. They stand about 9-10 inches tall at the shoulder. Their long, low body gives them a distinctive appearance.</p>',
                'coat_description' => '<p>This breed is known for its long, flowing double coat, which is weather-resistant. The outer coat is straight and harsh, while the undercoat is soft and dense. The Skye Terrier’s coat can come in various colors, including gray, cream, black, and fawn, often with a mix of these shades.</p>',
                'temperament_description' => '<p>Skye Terriers are known for being loyal, affectionate, and somewhat reserved with strangers. They are intelligent and can be quite independent, which may lead to stubbornness if not properly trained. They bond closely with their families and can be protective, making them good watchdogs.</p>',
                'lifestyle_description' => '<p>This breed does well in a home environment where they can be part of the family. While they enjoy some outdoor time, they are also content in an apartment or smaller living space as long as their exercise needs are met. Regular grooming is necessary to maintain their coat.</p>',
                'activities_description' => '<p>Skye Terriers can engage in various activities that cater to their physical and mental needs, including:</p><ul><li>Daily walks and play sessions</li><li>Basic obedience training and tricks</li><li>Agility and obstacle courses</li><li>Socialization with other dogs and people</li><li>Interactive toys and puzzle games</li></ul><p>Regular exercise and mental stimulation are essential for keeping Skye Terriers happy and healthy. Engaging them in activities helps prevent behavioral issues and supports their overall well-being.</p>',
                'hypoallergenic' => false,
                'created_at' => '2024-11-14 22:09:53',
                'updated_at' => '2024-11-14 22:13:17',
            ),
