            213 =>
            array (
                'id' => 238,
                'name' => 'Afghan Hound',
                'slug' => 'afghan-hound',
                'description' => NULL,
                'min_life' => 12,
                'max_life' => 14,
                'male_weight_max' => 27,
                'male_weight_min' => 23,
                'female_weight_max' => 25,
                'female_weight_min' => 20,
                'content' => NULL,
                'history_description' => '<p>The Afghan Hound is one of the oldest dog breeds, believed to have originated in the mountainous regions of Afghanistan. They were used as hunting dogs, particularly for large game like deer and leopards, due to their speed and agility. The breed has a rich history associated with nomadic tribes, and their distinctive appearance is adapted for survival in harsh climates.</p>',
                'size_description' => '<p>Afghan Hounds typically stand between <strong>24 to 29 inches</strong> tall at the shoulder. Males generally weigh between <strong>50 to 65 pounds</strong>, while females weigh between <strong>40 to 55 pounds</strong>.</p>',
                'coat_description' => '<p>The Afghan Hound has a long, flowing double coat that is silky and can come in various colors. They require regular grooming to prevent mats and tangles. Their coat is not only beautiful but also serves as protection against the elements in their native environment.</p>',
                'temperament_description' => '<p>Afghan Hounds are known for their independent and occasionally aloof nature. They tend to be gentle and affectionate with their families but may be reserved with strangers. They are intelligent dogs but can be somewhat stubborn, which means early training and socialization are important.</p>',
                'lifestyle_description' => '<p>Afghan Hounds thrive in active households. They are best suited for families who can provide them with plenty of exercise and mental stimulation. While they enjoy some downtime, they also need rigorous physical activity to stay healthy and happy.</p>',
                'activities_description' => '<p>Afghan Hounds love to run and can be great companions for activities such as:</p><ul><li><strong>Agility</strong>: They are quick and agile, making them good candidates for agility courses.</li><li><strong>Lure Coursing</strong>: Their natural hunting instincts make them excel in lure coursing events.</li><li><strong>Long walks or runs</strong>: They enjoy being outdoors and require regular exercise.</li><li><strong>Obedience training</strong>: Engaging them in training can provide mental stimulation.</li></ul>',
                'hypoallergenic' => false,
                'created_at' => '2024-11-14 22:09:53',
                'updated_at' => '2024-11-14 22:13:17',
            ),
