                'name' => 'Hanoverian Scenthound',
                'slug' => 'hanoverian-scenthound',
                'description' => NULL,
                'min_life' => 12,
                'max_life' => 14,
                'male_weight_max' => 25,
                'male_weight_min' => 20,
                'female_weight_max' => 25,
                'female_weight_min' => 20,
                'content' => NULL,
                'history_description' => '<p>The Hanoverian Scenthound, also known as the Hannoverscher Schweisshund, originated in Germany in the 18th century. Developed primarily for tracking large game, they were bred to have a keen sense of smell and stamina. This breed was widely used by hunters for tracking wounded game, making them invaluable in various hunting scenarios. Their history is interwoven with the pursuit of scent tracking, and they remain appreciated for their skills in this area. The breed is recognized by various kennel clubs, particularly in Germany and Europe.</p>',
                'size_description' => '<p>Hanoverian Scenthounds are medium to large-sized dogs. Males typically weigh between 55 to 65 pounds and stand approximately 19 to 23 inches tall at the shoulder, while females usually weigh between 45 to 55 pounds and stand about 18 to 22 inches tall. They have a strong, muscular build that reflects their working dog background.</p>',
                'coat_description' => '<p>The breed has a short, dense coat that is weather-resistant. The coat coloration can vary, typically featuring a combination of reddish-brown or tan, often with black markings. Their coat is relatively easy to maintain, generally requiring regular brushing to manage shedding and to keep it healthy.</p>',
                'temperament_description' => '<p>Hanoverian Scenthounds are known for their friendly and gentle nature. They are typically good-natured and get along well with other dogs and children, making them suitable for family environments. While they are intelligent and eager to please, they can be independent and should be provided with consistent training and socialization from an early age. Their strong instincts may also lead them to follow scents, so a well-fenced yard is advised.</p>',
                'lifestyle_description' => '<p>These dogs thrive in active lifestyles and require regular exercise to remain happy and healthy. Hanoverian Scenthounds do best in homes where they have space to roam and explore, as they are naturally curious and enjoy being outdoors. They can adapt to different living situations, but they need ample opportunities for physical activity and mental stimulation.</p>',
                'activities_description' => '<p>Hanoverian Scenthounds enjoy a variety of activities, including:</p><ul><li>Daily walks, runs, or hikes</li><li>Tracking and scent work, reflecting their heritage</li><li>Obedience training and agility exercises</li><li>Playtime in secure outdoor areas</li><li>Socialization outings to parks or dog-friendly events</li><li>Engaging in dog sports, such as scent trials</li></ul><p>These activities help fulfill their exercise and mental stimulation needs. Providing regular engagement and training will ensure a well-adjusted and happy Hanoverian Scenthound, making them delightful companions.</p>',
                'hypoallergenic' => false,
                'created_at' => '2024-11-14 22:09:53',
                'updated_at' => '2024-11-14 22:13:17',
            ),
            232 =>
            array (
                'id' => 253,
                'name' => 'Curly-Coated Retriever',
                'slug' => 'curly-coated-retriever',
                'description' => NULL,
                'min_life' => 12,
                'max_life' => 14,
                'male_weight_max' => 34,
                'male_weight_min' => 27,
                'female_weight_max' => 32,
                'female_weight_min' => 25,
                'content' => NULL,
                'history_description' => '<p>The Curly-Coated Retriever is one of the oldest retriever breeds, believed to have originated in England in the 19th century. They were developed primarily for hunting and retrieving game from water and land, often used by hunters for their ability to work in various environments. Their distinct curly coat provided protection against harsh weather conditions.</p>',
                'size_description' => '<p>Curly-Coated Retrievers are medium to large-sized dogs. Males typically weigh between 65-80 pounds and stand about 24-27 inches tall at the shoulder. Females are slightly smaller, weighing 50-70 pounds and standing 22-25 inches tall.</p>',
                'coat_description' => '<p>This breed is known for its unique, tight, water-resistant curly coat that sets it apart from other retrievers. The coat helps keep them warm in cold water and protects them from brambles and rough terrain. The coloring can vary, commonly found in solid black or liver.</p><p><br></p>',
                'temperament_description' => '<p>Curly-Coated Retrievers are known for being intelligent, confident, and independent, which can sometimes come off as aloofness. They are loyal and affectionate with their families but may be reserved with strangers. These dogs thrive on social interaction and require proper training and socialization.</p><p><br></p>',
                'lifestyle_description' => '<p>These dogs adapt well to various living situations but need ample exercise to stay healthy and happy. An active household is ideal, as they require regular mental and physical stimulation. They do best with owners who can provide consistent training and time for outdoor activities.</p>',
                'activities_description' => '<p>Curly-Coated Retrievers excel in a variety of activities, including:</p><ul><li>Obedience and agility training</li><li>Field trials and hunting</li><li>Swimming and water sports</li><li>Fetch and retrieval games</li><li>Canine sports like flyball or dock diving</li></ul><p>Regular exercise and engagement in these activities are crucial to prevent boredom and destructive behavior.</p>',
                'hypoallergenic' => false,
                'created_at' => '2024-11-14 22:09:53',
                'updated_at' => '2024-11-14 22:13:17',
            ),
