                'min_life' => 12,
                'max_life' => 15,
                'male_weight_max' => 7,
                'male_weight_min' => 6,
                'female_weight_max' => 7,
                'female_weight_min' => 6,
                'content' => NULL,
                'history_description' => '<p>The Smooth Fox Terrier originated in England in the 19th century and was bred primarily for hunting foxes. It stems from a cross between various terrier breeds, including the now-extinct Black and Tan Terrier and other working breeds. The Smooth Fox Terrier quickly distinguished itself from the Rough Fox Terrier due to its short, smooth coat and was recognized by kennel clubs in the early 20th century.</p>',
            'size_description' => '<ul><li><strong>Height:</strong> Typically stands between 14 to 15.5 inches (36 to 39 cm) at the shoulder.</li><li><strong>Weight:</strong> Generally weighs around 15 to 18 pounds (7 to 8 kg).</li></ul><p><br></p>',
                'coat_description' => '<p>The Smooth Fox Terrier features a short, dense, and flat-lying coat that is weather-resistant. The coat is predominantly white with black and/or tan markings. Because of the short coat, grooming is relatively easy, requiring only occasional brushing to remove loose hair.</p>',
                'temperament_description' => '<p>The Smooth Fox Terrier is known for its:</p><ul><li>Energetic and playful nature, making them great companions for active families.</li><li>Intelligent and alert personality, often displaying curiosity and a strong prey drive.</li><li>Friendly disposition, usually getting along well with children and other pets when properly socialized.</li><li>Tenacious and sometimes stubborn temperament, which can make training a challenge if not approached with consistency and patience.</li></ul>',
                'lifestyle_description' => '<p>This breed thrives in an active household where they can participate in family activities. Belgian Tervurens adapt well to a variety of living situations, but they do best in environments where they have space to run and play. Due to their intelligence and energy, they require regular exercise and engagement.</p>',
                'activities_description' => '<p>Smooth Fox Terriers enjoy a variety of activities, including:</p><ul><li>Regular walks, jogs, or play sessions to expend their energy.</li><li>Engaging in dog sports such as agility, obedience, and flyball.</li><li>Participating in games that stimulate their hunting instincts, like fetch or scent work.</li><li>Socialization opportunities with other dogs, people, and environments to help curb any excess energy or stubbornness.</li></ul><p>Overall, the Smooth Fox Terrier is a vibrant, affectionate, and intelligent breed that requires an active lifestyle and consistent training to flourish as a beloved companion.</p>',
                'hypoallergenic' => false,
                'created_at' => '2024-11-14 22:09:53',
                'updated_at' => '2024-11-14 22:13:17',
            ),
            239 =>
            array (
                'id' => 259,
                'name' => 'Bergamasco Sheepdog',
                'slug' => 'bergamasco-sheepdog',
                'description' => NULL,
                'min_life' => 12,
                'max_life' => 15,
                'male_weight_max' => 45,
                'male_weight_min' => 25,
                'female_weight_max' => 45,
                'female_weight_min' => 25,
                'content' => NULL,
                'history_description' => '<p>The Bergamasco Sheepdog is an ancient breed that hails from the Italian Alps, particularly the region of Bergamo. They were developed over centuries as versatile working dogs primarily used for herding and protecting livestock. Their unique coat helped them withstand harsh weather conditions and provided protection against predators. The breed has remained relatively unchanged over time, maintaining its traditional herding and guarding instincts.</p>',
                'size_description' => '<p>Bergamasco Sheepdogs are medium to large-sized dogs. Males typically weigh between 70-84 pounds and stand about 23-25 inches tall at the shoulder. Females are slightly smaller, weighing 57-71 pounds and standing 20-23 inches tall. They are robust and sturdy, reflecting their working heritage.</p>',
                'coat_description' => '<p>One of the most distinctive features of the Bergamasco Sheepdog is its unique coat, which consists of three types of hair: a short undercoat, long guard hair, and felted hair that forms natural "flocks" as they mature. The coat is dense, weather-resistant, and can come in various colors, including gray, black, and tawny. Regular grooming is essential to maintain the coat’s health and prevent matting, although their grooming needs differ from those of other breeds due to its unique texture.</p>',
                'temperament_description' => '<p>Bergamasco Sheepdogs are known for their intelligence, loyalty, and calm demeanor. They are typically affectionate with family members and can be reserved with strangers. They are natural protectors, making them good watchdogs. These dogs are eager to learn but require consistent training, as they can sometimes exhibit a stubborn streak.</p>',
                'lifestyle_description' => '<p>Bergamasco Sheepdogs adapt well to various living situations but do best in homes where they can have access to a yard and participate in outdoor activities. They thrive in active families who can provide them with attention and engagement. Regular interactions and socialization are important to keep them well-adjusted.</p>',
                'activities_description' => '<p>Bergamasco Sheepdogs enjoy several activities that cater to their physical and mental needs, including:</p><ul><li>Daily walks and outdoor play</li><li>Herding or obedience training</li><li>Participating in dog sports like agility or herding trials</li><li>Hiking and outdoor adventures</li><li>Interactive play with family members and games that challenge their minds</li></ul><p>Overall, providing consistent exercise and mental stimulation is crucial for keeping a Bergamasco Sheepdog happy and healthy, as they thrive on activity and companionship.</p>',
                'hypoallergenic' => false,
                'created_at' => '2024-11-14 22:09:53',
                'updated_at' => '2024-11-14 22:13:17',
            ),
